work with github
terms:
-repo (it contains the collection of file - project folder)
-commit (the latest snapshot of a project/ save all the changes)
-hash (the unique commit ID)
-checkout (A checkout is the act of switching between different versions of a target entity)
-branch (independent line of development)
-merge (join two or more development histories together)
-remote (It is a secondary copy of a Git repository where you push changes for collaboration or backup)
-clone (Clone operation copies remote repository into local) 
-push (sending committed changes to a remote repository)
-pull (opposite of push)
